        "output": "{'id': 'res_001', 'name': 'Alice Chen', 'yoe_react': 6, 'yoe_python': 7, 'education': \"PhD Computer Science, Stanford University (2020). BS Electrical Engineering & Computer Science, MIT (2014). Thesis: 'Distributed consensus protocols for byzantine-tolerant ML systems'.\", 'highlights': 'Currently Staff Engineer at Anthropic (2023-present), leading platform infrastructure for Claude API serving 100M+ daily requests. Previously Senior SWE at Stripe (2017-2023), where she designed the rate-limiting tier serving 100M+ requests/day. Open-source contributor to React Suspense (3 merged PRs) and FastAPI (core team alumna). Patents: 2 on distributed transaction reconciliation. Co-author of 4 papers on serverless ML inference, cited 120+ times. References available from Stripe CTO and Anthropic infra lead.'}",
